---

<PageLayout meta={{ title: "About" }}>
	<section class="mt-8 flex flex-col gap-10">
		{/* HEADER: title + affiliations */}
		<div class="text-text max-w-3xl space-y-4">
			<p class="text-2xl font-semibold">M.Sc. Computer Science · AI Research</p>

			<div class="flex items-center gap-2 text-lg">
				<!-- Books Icon -->
				<svg
					xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
					class="text-accent h-6 w-6"
					fill="none"
					viewBox="0 0 24 24"
					stroke="currentColor"
					stroke-width="1.5"
				>
					<path
						stroke-linecap="round"
						stroke-linejoin="round"
						d="M12 6.75c0-1.243 1.007-2.25 2.25-2.25H21v13.5h-6.75A2.25 2.25 0 0 0 12 20.25V6.75zM3 6.75c0-1.243 1.007-2.25 2.25-2.25H12v13.5H5.25A2.25 2.25 0 0 1 3 15.75V6.75z"
					></path>
				</svg>

				<!-- Institutions -->
				<span class="flex gap-2 font-medium">
					<a
						href="https://www.umontreal.ca/"
						target="_blank"
						rel="noopener noreferrer"
						class="text-accent underline underline-offset-2"
					>
						Université de Montréal
					</a>
					<span>·</span>
					<a
						href="https://mila.quebec/"
						target="_blank"
						rel="noopener noreferrer"
						class="text-accent underline underline-offset-2"
					>
						Mila – Quebec AI Institute
					</a>
				</span>
			</div>
		</div>

		{/* BODY TEXT: smaller + airy */}
		<div class="text-text max-w-3xl space-y-4 text-sm leading-relaxed sm:text-base">
			<p>
				I am a <strong>M.Sc. Computer Science Research Student</strong> specializing in
				<strong> Artificial Intelligence</strong> at the <strong>Université de Montréal</strong>
				and <strong>Mila – Quebec AI Institute</strong>.
			</p>

			<p>
				My work sits at the intersection of <strong>machine learning</strong>,
				<strong> reinforcement learning</strong>, and <strong>graph-structured data</strong>. I am
				particularly interested in how intelligent agents can reason over
				<strong> dynamic, interconnected systems</strong> like <strong>power grids</strong>.
			</p>

			<p>
				I study how we can design agents that understand structure, adapt to changes, and make
				reliable decisions in environments with large action spaces and evolving graph topology.
			</p>

			<p>
				More broadly, I aim to advance the foundations of decision-making in
				<strong> large and dynamic graph environments</strong> — and apply these methods to build more
				<strong> sustainable</strong> and <strong>resilient</strong> real-world systems.
			</p>
		</div>

		{/* Social links */}
		<SocialList />
	</section>
</PageLayout>
